 Citations )
  
    Incremental and decremental maintenance of planar width . 
D. Eppstein.  arXiv:cs.CG/9809038 .  
 10th ACM-SIAM Symp. Discrete Algorithms, 
Baltimore, 1999, pp. S899-S900 .   J.
Algorithms  37 (2): 570–577, 2000 .
 
We show how to maintain the width of a planar point set, subject to
insertions or deletions (but not both) in time
O( n   c  ) per update for any  c  &gt; 0.
The idea is to apply our  dynamic closest pair
data structure  to an appropriate measure of distance between
pairs of convex hull features.
